Baroness Margaret Thatcher, the first female Prime Minister of Britain, has passed away. President Obama expressed his condolences and praised her as a champion of freedom and liberty. He highlighted her rise from being a grocer's daughter to becoming a powerful leader, serving as an inspiration for women to break through glass ceilings. Thatcher restored confidence and pride in Britain, and as a strong supporter of the transatlantic alliance, she played a key role in winning the Cold War. The President mentioned her close partnership with President Reagan, emphasizing their shared belief in shaping history with moral conviction, courage, and determination. President Obama and his wife, Michelle, sent their thoughts to the Thatcher family and the British people, affirming their commitment to continue the work she dedicated her life to - uniting free nations in writing their own destiny.